The paper deals with the computation of geodesic distance in graphics applications, which is a common problem in computer graphics (cs.CG) and geometric modeling (cs.GR). The proposed algorithm is based on a discrete approach, which involves data structures and algorithms (cs.DS) and distributed computing (cs.DC). The paper also mentions the use of GPUs for implementation, which falls under computer vision (cs.CV) as well.
